OL,6,F"So they are balloting their members
OL,7,Fwith regard to strike action, not
OL,8,Findustrial action, strike action
OL,9,Fspecifically, and they've said if
OL,10,Fthey're going out on strike this time,
OL,11,Fthere'll be no derogations, there will
OL,12,Fbe no mitigations.
OL,14,F"So, unless something changes, I'm
OL,15,Fafraid we have to anticipate nurses on
OL,16,Fthe street by mid-November. And what
OL,17,Fthat does to the waiting list
OL,18,Finitiative in the programme for
OL,19,Fgovernment, what it does to health and
OL,20,Fsocial care and delivery, is just
OL,21,Fmassive."
